ðŸ“„ Business Requirements Document (BRD)

Customer Churn Analysis Dashboard

1. Document Overview

1.1 Project Name

Customer Churn Analysis â€“ Power BI Dashboard

1.2 Prepared By

Business Analyst / Data Analyst

1.3 Objective

To analyze customer churn behavior, identify churn drivers, assess customer risk, and provide actionable recommendations to reduce churn and improve customer retention.

2. Business Background

Customer churn has a direct impact on:

Revenue loss

Customer Lifetime Value (CLV)

Increased acquisition costs

The business requires a data-driven dashboard to:

Monitor churn metrics

Identify at-risk customers early

Understand factors contributing to churn

Support proactive retention strategies

3. Business Problem Statement

The organization lacks visibility into:

Why customers are leaving

Which customer segments are most at risk

How churn impacts revenue

Where intervention can reduce churn

Without actionable insights, retention efforts are reactive instead of proactive.

4. Stakeholders
Role	Responsibility
Business Leadership	Strategic decision-making
Customer Success Team	Retention actions
Operations Team	Service improvement
Business Analyst	Requirements & insights
Data Analyst	Data modeling & dashboards

5. Scope
5.1 In Scope

Customer churn rate analysis

Customer segmentation (contract, tenure, payment method, services)

Revenue impact of churn

Funnel analysis for churn lifecycle

Interactive Power BI dashboard

5.2 Out of Scope

Predictive churn modeling

Real-time data ingestion

CRM system integration

6. Business Requirements
6.1 Functional Requirements
ID	Requirement
BR-01	Display total customers and churned customers
BR-02	Calculate churn rate (%)
BR-03	Identify customers at risk of churn
BR-04	Analyze churn by contract type
BR-05	Analyze churn by payment method
BR-06	Analyze churn by internet service
BR-07	Analyze churn by tenure
BR-08	Show revenue impact of churn
BR-09	Provide funnel analysis of customer lifecycle
BR-10	Enable filtering by customer attributes

6.2 Non-Functional Requirements

Category	Requirement
Performance	Dashboard should load within 5 seconds
Usability	Simple, executive-friendly layout
Maintainability	Measures reusable and documented
Scalability	Should support additional customer data

7. Data Requirements
7.1 Data Sources

Customer master data

Subscription and billing data

Service usage data

Support ticket data

7.2 Key Data Fields

Customer ID

Churn status

Tenure

Contract type

Payment method

Monthly charges

Total charges

Internet service

Support tickets

8. KPIs & Metrics
KPI	Description
Total Customers	Total active customer base
Churned Customers	Customers who left
Churn Rate (%)	% of customers churned
Customers at Risk	High-risk churn segment
Monthly Charges	Average customer spend
Revenue Lost	Revenue from churned customers

