9.2 Business Purpose

Identify early churn signals

Detect maximum drop-off stage

Support targeted retention strategies

10. Dashboard Requirements
10.1 Pages
Page 1: Executive Overview

KPI summary

Key insights

Business recommendations

Page 2: Churn Analysis

Churn by contract type

Churn by tenure

Churn by payment method

Service-level churn analysis

Page 3: Customer Risk Analysis

High-risk customer identification

Revenue impact

Support ticket correlation

11. Assumptions

Data provided is accurate and complete

Churn definition is binary (Yes / No)

Monthly charges reflect current pricing

Tenure is measured in months

12. Constraints

Historical data only (no real-time updates)

Limited to available dataset fields

No machine learning implementation

13. Risks & Mitigation
Risk	Mitigation
Data quality issues	Data validation & cleansing
Misinterpretation of churn drivers	Clear definitions & documentation
Stakeholder misalignment	Regular review checkpoints

14. Business Recommendations (High-Level)

Promote long-term contracts to reduce churn

Improve service quality for high-churn services

Incentivize automatic payment methods

Target early-tenure customers with onboarding programs

15. Success Criteria

Clear identification of churn drivers

Actionable insights for retention

Improved decision-making capability

Dashboard adoption by business stakeholders

